Web page : http : / / www . rd . nacsis . ac . jp / ~ andres / qpmids 99 . html The development of the cyberspace society and the increasing use of multimedia and hypermedia technology will influence how society access to cultural material . In this context , the QPMIDS workshop seeks to bring together all major players : users such as museums , and cultural heritage holders , researchers and industrial developers working in the field of distributed multimedia information systems to assess the state of the art and practical solutions in multimedia cultural applications , and also to introduce promising future research issues such as real-time multimedia data processing , virtual one-line multimedia management , or multimedia distance learning systems . To our opinion , these applications are one of the most challenging and the most critical for the success of future world wide information systems . The QPMIDS workshop is to be a forum for free exchange of ideas . Particularly welcome are reports on experimental work , experience with current standards and position papers addressing current and future needs of distributed multimedia and hypermedia systems . Topics for submission include but are not limited to : . Modeling of multimedia and hypermedia data . Multimedia database architecture . Distributed multidimensional multimedia information systems . Distributed and parallel multimedia query processing and query optimization . QoS ( load balancing , data placement ) issues in multimedia information system . Virtual reality management . Multimedia distance learning system . Standards and language for multimedia information / database systems . Benchmarking of distributed multimedia systems . Multimedia and Media Mining . Copyright and protection of the multimedia and hypermedia information Submission = = = = = = = = = = Short original contributions or demonstration regarding the problem solving and / or aims for further research activities in the workshop topics are welcome . Extended abstract papers or position papers should be in English and not exceed 5 double spaced pages or 1000 words . The cover page should include the title , name and affiliation of the author ( s ) , contact , address , email , fax and telephone . Final paper should not exceed 10 single spaced pages .
